WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:21.560
Sarah says no by Norman Whitney.

00:21.560 --> 00:23.960
Welcome to Middletown.

00:23.960 --> 00:27.320
It is Monday morning.

00:27.320 --> 00:30.120
Mr. Frute is at the market.

00:30.120 --> 00:32.960
The market is busy.

00:32.960 --> 00:37.760
Today there is a new man at the market.

00:37.760 --> 00:41.400
His name is Mr. Frute.

00:41.400 --> 00:44.600
His daughter is helping him.

00:44.600 --> 00:47.720
Her name is Sarah.

00:47.720 --> 00:49.640
Good morning.

00:49.640 --> 00:52.520
Mr. Frute says to everybody.

00:52.520 --> 00:54.680
My fruit is fresh.

00:54.680 --> 00:57.240
My fruit is cheap.

00:57.240 --> 01:00.200
Mr. Frute is polite.

01:00.200 --> 01:02.880
He is friendly.

01:02.880 --> 01:06.520
Everybody likes Mr. Frute.

01:06.520 --> 01:09.440
What a nice man.

01:09.440 --> 01:14.920
They say, everybody likes his daughter.

01:14.920 --> 01:17.720
What a nice girl.

01:17.720 --> 01:25.920
They say, a school boy asks for one kilo of apples.

01:25.920 --> 01:30.960
Mr. Frute puts some apples on the scales.

01:30.960 --> 01:37.320
The scales show one kilo and 100 grams.

01:37.320 --> 01:41.640
Mr. Frute takes one apple away.

01:41.640 --> 01:47.080
Now the scales show 900 grams.

01:47.080 --> 01:53.480
But Mr. Frute says, one kilo of apples, one dollar.

01:53.480 --> 01:57.760
He takes one dollar from the school boy.

01:57.760 --> 02:01.000
Sarah is watching her father.

02:01.000 --> 02:02.800
She sees everything.

02:05.880 --> 02:11.920
A young woman asks for two kilos of oranges.

02:11.920 --> 02:17.160
Mr. Frute puts some oranges on the scales.

02:17.160 --> 02:23.120
The scales show two kilos and 200 grams.

02:23.120 --> 02:27.400
Mr. Frute takes one orange away.

02:27.400 --> 02:34.240
Now the scales show one kilo and 800 grams.

02:34.240 --> 02:41.320
But Mr. Frute says, two kilos of oranges, two dollars.

02:41.320 --> 02:45.720
He takes two dollars from the young woman.

02:45.720 --> 02:48.000
Sarah sees everything.

02:48.160 --> 02:51.240
It is Monday evening.

02:51.240 --> 02:55.440
Sarah's father is counting his money.

02:55.440 --> 02:57.440
He is happy.

02:57.440 --> 03:00.600
But Sarah is not happy.

03:00.600 --> 03:02.600
She is angry.

03:07.240 --> 03:13.080
Father, you must sell the correct weight.

03:13.080 --> 03:17.960
You mustn't sell the correct weight.

03:17.960 --> 03:22.640
Cheetah customers, our customers are poor.

03:22.640 --> 03:25.560
But we are poor too, Sarah.

03:25.560 --> 03:27.480
My wife is dead.

03:27.480 --> 03:29.600
You have no mother.

03:29.600 --> 03:32.120
I have no sons.

03:32.120 --> 03:34.400
You have no brothers.

03:34.400 --> 03:36.600
We must make money, Sarah.

03:36.600 --> 03:38.560
That's life.

03:38.560 --> 03:42.160
I don't want to work at the market, Father.

03:42.160 --> 03:44.520
You must work at the market.

03:44.520 --> 03:46.560
We must live, Sarah.

03:46.560 --> 03:48.480
We must eat.

03:48.480 --> 03:50.560
You're a child.

03:50.560 --> 03:53.680
You don't understand business.

03:53.680 --> 03:55.240
You're a woman.

03:55.240 --> 03:58.400
Women don't understand business.

03:58.400 --> 03:59.680
That's life, Sarah.

04:07.600 --> 04:10.200
It is Tuesday morning.

04:10.200 --> 04:15.480
Today, Sarah's father is selling the correct weight.

04:15.480 --> 04:17.520
He is honest.

04:17.520 --> 04:20.520
He takes the correct money.

04:20.520 --> 04:22.800
Sarah is happy.

04:22.800 --> 04:27.120
Today, she is proud of her father.

04:27.120 --> 04:30.440
The customers are happy too.

04:30.440 --> 04:34.040
They buy a lot of fruit.

04:34.040 --> 04:37.960
Your fruit is cheap and fresh.

04:37.960 --> 04:40.760
They say.

04:40.760 --> 04:45.480
But in the afternoon, some customers come back.

04:45.480 --> 04:47.800
They are angry.

04:47.800 --> 04:51.960
An old man brings back some apples.

04:51.960 --> 04:55.600
One of his apples is bad.

04:55.600 --> 04:59.360
A girl brings back some oranges.

04:59.360 --> 05:03.160
One of her oranges is bad.

05:03.160 --> 05:06.640
A woman brings back some bananas.

05:06.640 --> 05:10.080
One of her bananas is bad.

05:10.080 --> 05:14.560
It is black and full of worms.

05:14.560 --> 05:16.960
Look, Mr. Fruit.

05:16.960 --> 05:20.440
Your fruit isn't fresh today.

05:20.440 --> 05:24.400
We want our money back.

05:24.400 --> 05:28.160
But Mr. Fruit does not listen.

05:28.160 --> 05:30.480
He does not give them any money.

05:35.520 --> 05:39.520
Your dishonest father says, Sarah,

05:39.520 --> 05:42.240
you're cheating the customers.

05:42.240 --> 05:44.840
I don't want to work for you.

05:44.840 --> 05:48.080
I don't want to work at the market.

05:48.080 --> 05:50.920
But you must work for me, Sarah.

05:50.920 --> 05:52.480
Says her father.

05:52.480 --> 05:54.440
I have no family.

05:54.440 --> 05:57.800
I have no wife and no sons.

05:57.800 --> 06:00.800
Children must help their parents.

06:00.800 --> 06:02.680
You are my daughter, Sarah.

06:02.680 --> 06:04.520
You must work for me.

06:04.520 --> 06:05.960
That's life.

06:05.960 --> 06:07.720
No father.

06:07.720 --> 06:09.240
Says Sarah.

06:09.240 --> 06:12.120
I don't want to clean your house.

06:12.120 --> 06:14.320
I want to leave home.

06:14.320 --> 06:17.480
I don't want to cook your food.

06:17.480 --> 06:20.240
I want to get a good job.

06:20.240 --> 06:23.880
I'm not going to work for you.

06:23.880 --> 06:26.440
Sarah's father is angry.

06:26.440 --> 06:28.040
Go to bed.

06:28.040 --> 06:29.400
He shouts at her.

06:32.440 --> 06:34.600
Sarah goes to bed.

06:34.600 --> 06:36.720
She is lonely.

06:36.720 --> 06:38.960
She is unhappy.

06:38.960 --> 06:41.440
She says a prayer.

06:41.440 --> 06:43.800
Please help me.

06:43.800 --> 06:46.760
Please help my father.

06:46.760 --> 06:48.440
Please help us.

06:51.360 --> 06:54.200
What am I going to do?

06:54.200 --> 06:57.320
I need a miracle.

06:57.320 --> 06:58.320
Help me.

07:03.160 --> 07:05.800
It is Wednesday morning.

07:05.800 --> 07:08.920
Everybody is at the market.

07:08.920 --> 07:11.880
Everybody is laughing.

07:11.880 --> 07:15.720
Something strange is happening.

07:15.720 --> 07:19.600
Mr. Fruit touches an apple.

07:19.600 --> 07:23.080
The apple goes bad.

07:23.080 --> 07:25.960
Then he picks up an orange.

07:25.960 --> 07:29.440
The orange goes bad, too.

07:29.440 --> 07:33.080
Then he picks up some bananas.

07:33.080 --> 07:35.840
They go black.

07:35.880 --> 07:37.880
Everybody laughs.

07:42.080 --> 07:44.640
Look at Mr. Fruit.

07:44.640 --> 07:50.200
He touches the fruit and it goes bad.

07:50.200 --> 07:54.440
Mr. Fruit looks at his hands.

07:54.440 --> 07:56.360
What is happening?

07:56.360 --> 07:59.400
He says, please, Sarah.

07:59.400 --> 08:02.600
Please help me.

08:02.600 --> 08:05.480
Sarah touches an apple.

08:05.480 --> 08:09.920
She picks up an orange and some bananas.

08:09.920 --> 08:12.320
Hooray!

08:12.320 --> 08:17.280
Everybody says, it's a miracle.

08:17.280 --> 08:22.600
Sarah touches the fruit and it's OK.

08:22.600 --> 08:26.120
We're going to buy our fruit from Sarah.

08:27.120 --> 08:33.120
Next year, Mr. Fruit is mis-fruit.

08:33.120 --> 08:36.120
Sarah is honest.

08:36.120 --> 08:39.120
She does not cheat.

08:39.120 --> 08:43.120
She always sells the correct weight.

08:43.120 --> 08:46.120
She sells good, fresh fruit.

08:46.120 --> 08:49.120
She understands business.

08:49.120 --> 08:53.120
Sarah is not the best.

08:54.120 --> 08:57.120
Sarah is making a lot of money.

08:57.120 --> 09:02.120
She has a good job now.

09:02.120 --> 09:05.120
Sarah's father stays at home.

09:05.120 --> 09:08.120
He cleans the house.

09:08.120 --> 09:10.120
He cooks the food.

09:10.120 --> 09:12.120
He is very happy.

09:12.120 --> 09:14.120
That's life.

09:14.120 --> 09:17.120
He says.

09:23.120 --> 09:28.120
MUSIC

